{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Cease plans to make changes to the Work Capability Assessment (WCA)",
        "additional_details": "I believe that the changes would lead to more disabled people being incorrectly found fit for work, more at risk of having their benefits sanctioned, and fewer classed as having limited capability for work / work related activity. The proposals have already provoked strong opposition from Disabled People's Organisations (DPOs) and the Royal College of Psychiatrists (RCPsych).",
        "background": "I believe plans to remove or change some descriptors used to assess whether certain disabilities reduce people\u2019s ability to work, and to amend the \u201csubstantial risk\u201d regulations, are profoundly unethical and unjustifiable.",
